Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Springmonth 2 13:45:00. Player: I place the small chest of gold on the table and slide it to Elen. This is yours, you earned it. I retain the deed though for now.

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "The firelight flickers over the battered small coffer as you set it on the table and gently slide it toward Elen. The chatter in the inn quiets a little, a few villagers glancing over with curiosity.\n\nElen looks at the chest, then meets your gaze with startled gratitude. \"Norn, you don't have to... I only did what anyone ought to, but... thank you.\" She opens the lid, eyes widening at the gold and gemstones within. For a moment, her voice is thick with emotion. \"The keep's curse was never just my burden--but I'll use this to help the village. There are too many here who have lost too much.\"\n\nShe closes the chest and places her hand over yours, earnest and resolute. \"Keep the deed. You faced what I couldn't and brought me home. Maybe one day, Shadowfall Keep will be more than a memory of fear. For now, let's see to the living.\"\n\nCira, watching from behind the bar, raises an approving eyebrow. \"That's the Hollow's spirit right there. Drinks on the house for our heroes!\"\n\nThe moment lingers, warm and hopeful, as laughter and conversation swell once more around you.",
