Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "The Wyrd Lantern Inn welcomes you with the familiar glow of lanternlight and the soft murmur of contented villagers. The scent of fresh bread and stewed meat drifts from the kitchen, and Cira catches your eye from behind the bar, offering a wave and a knowing smile. Elen is still at your table near the hearth, finishing her meal and deep in quiet conversation with a pair of wide-eyed children eager for tales of the Gloamwood. As you settle back into your seat, Elen glances your way and grins. \"Welcome back, Norn. I was just telling them about the time you nearly mistook a spectral scribe's chair for a mimic again.\"\n\nThe mood in the inn is one of warmth and celebration, the village's fears replaced by laughter and hope. The fire crackles, and the moment is yours to shape. What would you like to do next?",
  "actions": []
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Springmonth 2 13:50:00. Player: Oh really! that mimic was a beast, what a fight!

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "Elen laughs, her shoulders finally at ease. \"It really was! You should have seen their faces,\" she says, gesturing to the two children at the table, who giggle in delight. \"Norn just about toppled the scribe's entire desk when that chair lashed out at him.\"\n\nOne of the children, a freckled boy with wild hair, leans forward eagerly. \"Did you really slay a monster disguised as furniture? How did you know it wasn't just... you know... a chair?\"\n\nCira, catching the tale from behind the bar, chimes in with a wink, \"That's why I always knock twice before I sit down in the morning! You never know in a place as old as this.\"\n\nElen grins. \"Norn's quick reflexes saved the day, but it was teamwork that carried us through all of it. And a little luck, maybe some clever thinking, and the promise of a hot meal at the end.\"\n\nThe children stare at you, eyes wide with anticipation. \"Were you scared?\" one whispers. The inn grows quiet for a moment, as if the whole common room is waiting to hear how you faced the terrors of Shadowfall Keep.",
  "actions": [
