      }
    }
  ]
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Springmonth 2 13:55:00. Player: I was very scared! They have sharp teeth and are very scary! But, i was careful and i saw it brath just slightly and shift. The beast was hungry!

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "The children gasp, hanging on every word. One clutches his wooden toy sword a little tighter, eyes wide. \"You mean it really breathed, like a monster hiding in plain sight?\" he whispers.\n\nElen leans in, her tone conspiratorial but warm. \"That's why you always trust your instincts in old places, and keep good company. Norn here didn't flinch, even when that thing snapped its jaws right at his boots.\"\n\nThe inn erupts in gentle laughter as Cira shakes her head. \"Just as well you both made it back in one piece. Shadows and monsters, but it's the clever ones who come home.\"\n\nA middle-aged woman at a nearby table nods to you. \"If you could spot a monster in disguise, maybe you'll help us spot any trouble that tries to sneak back into the Hollow. We sleep easier knowing you two are watching.\"\n\nElen meets your gaze, a smile bright but sincere. \"I suppose we make a good team after all. What do you think, Norn? Ready for another adventure, or is it time we let someone else check under the chairs for a while?\"\n\nThe room is filled with warmth and hope, the story of your courage already spreading among those gathered. For this moment, the terrors of Shadowfall Keep remain only a tale--a warning, and a source of pride.",
  "actions": [
