Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You stand, stretching as the warmth of the hearth lulls you into a well-earned sense of safety. Elen gives you a wry smile, her expression understanding. \"Take your time, Norn. You've earned a moment's peace. We'll be here when you return--and I'll be sure to keep a watchful eye on any chairs that look a bit too eager.\"\n\nAround you, the villagers continue sharing stories and laughter, the inn alive with the spirit of celebration. The sense of hope you've helped restore lingers, wrapping you in comfort as you prepare to step away. The Wyrd Lantern Inn now feels more like home than ever.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "exitGame",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Resume the game, the player has returned.

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "The familiar glow of lanterns welcomes you back to the Wyrd Lantern Inn. The hum of friendly conversation and the scent of fresh bread drift through the air, as if no time has passed at all. Elen glances up from the hearth, where she sits chatting with a pair of villagers, and her face brightens with a smile. \"Back so soon, Norn? I was just telling them how close you came to sitting on that mimic after all!\" she teases, laughter in her voice.\n\nThe inn is alive with warmth and camaraderie, and the villagers' spirits are high. The fireside feels inviting, and the promise of good company and well-deserved rest lingers in the air. As you reclaim your seat by Elen, Cira brings over a fresh mug and a plate of food, winking approvingly.\n\nThe peace you've won for Harrow's Hollow is palpable tonight. What would you like to do next?",
  "actions": []
}

